text.tspan: Plugins add their docks and menu entries by themselves
Timeline abstraction to allow different timeline views,
e.g. the current view and a view specialised on handling transitions
Supports transitions on the same track (new feature)
Tools like trim, move, and select need to be considered
Shows clips in the project, in a tree or list
Lists available effects, allows to search by name
Effects can be grouped (tree structure) by properties
Editor for effects in an EffectList (from the Model)
Editor layers on top of Monitors and TimelineClips;
allow editing special property types like Bzier areas on the monitor
or keyframeable volumes on the timeline (latter would be disabled
in the timeline view specialised on transitions)
Maintains selections of tracks and clips on a timeline (one TISM per timeline)
Knows focused elements (either tracks or clips)
EffectStack is notified when the selection changes and can update itself
accordingly (has access to TISM, Core, etc.)
Widget for seeking in the monitor
Should be created with QML and using GLSL
Supports on-monitor editing (e.g. rotoscoping) via layers
Font used: Source Sans Pro, Source Code Pro
Architecture according to refactoring goals by Till Theato
In Inkscape, you can copy elements (Ctrl+C) and paste formatting only (Shift+Ctrl+V)
e.g. to apply marker styles (is-a arrows) and box colours.
Use the alignment feature (Shift+Ctrl+A) to align left borders or to balance space between objects.
